reviews: Typical Parisian hotel in a nice area of the city. 3 metro stations just within walking distance. Good caf√©s and bistros right in the area around the hotel. The rooms also OK size. And the breakfast is also fine.

I‚Äôm a fan of Ibis with their sensible approach to quality versus unnecessary luxuries, reasonable prices and good locations.
However I was extremely disappointed this time.
The breakfast was good, the location was great and their staff was friendly.
But the bedroom was terrible. Small like I‚Äôd never seen, there was barely space to walk around the bed and the entry to the shower was so narrow that it had to be done sideways (with a step and the corner of the lavatory adding to the difficulty).
The bed was hard and uncomfortable.
I won‚Äôt stay here again.

The location of this Hotel is what immediately attracted us to stay here - there's no denying it's in a great spot. Walking distance from the louvre and montmartre.

The majority of the photos of the hotel seem to be advertising the foyer, reception and dining area which are all relatively modern and nicely decorated. However our room really wasn't great and I would have expected much more for the price of around ¬£200 per night. We went on NYE so this may have increased the price we paid, however the 4 star trip advisor rating also was not reflected in the room.

Our en suite was a wet room with a blocked shower drain that flooded the entire bathroom every time one of us took a shower. It also smelt really quite bad in the bathroom and generally didn't really feel very clean.

My last gripe would be that they took ¬£200 out of my account 7 days before I arrived at the hotel and still hasn't been returned 5 days after checking out (this is out-with the cost of the room which was paid in full on arrival). I don't believe I was told this would happen when I booked the room and this has never happened to me before so I am quite annoyed about it. I've never had any kind of 'deposit' taken from my account days before arriving at a hotel and not been given it back for further days after.

Despite this the staff were very friendly and helpful and our stay wasn't impacted by the quality of room.

The moment I got an email from Mariam, the hotel staff few days before we arrived asking us how they could make our stay more comfortable, i knew we were in for a good stay. i was actually excited because our previous stay with Ibis Styles Bercy was a big letdown & worst experience we had in an Ibis Hotel chain. We checked in a bit earlier that usual around 12:30pm and usually check in time was 2pm and violaaa, our room was ready! Plus we got our welcome drinks as part of being an Accor Silver member. A great way to start our day in Paris! When we got into our room i was so impressed, the rooms was clean and it was larger than what you expect in an Ibis hotel, it was well lit with 2 windows that has view of the street which was AMAZING and the entire room was even carpeted! For a while i thought i was staying at Novotel! It has amenties that will make you feel comfortable and not cramped like it has spacious cabinet with dividers & hangers, long dresser table to place your stuff and has even a small cozy space near the window with a small table and comfy chair. The bed was clean and linens and towels are changed daily if you request it. Toilet was larger than usual, like twice larger than the one weve stayed in before! The hotel has impeccable location, it was just few meters away from 3 metro stations, the nearest is Le Peletier M7 line, the vibe of the neighborhood is very Parisian with a lot of cafes, resto, grocery store, fast food and hidden bistros in the area you can explore. You can even walk to the Lourve Museum, Grand Palais and Grand La Fayette shopping from here for 10-15min. Overall, it was the best stay we had in Paris & France in terms of location, amenities & service. I wanted to give it a 10/10 but i have issues with the shower gel that was not refilled in our 5 day stay & the noise of the adjacent room so just 8/10 for now. If its your first time to go in Paris & youre on a budget but want to have a comfortable stay, look no further & book this hotel! I will be definitely staying here again when I come back to Paris. I hope the hotel maintains & improve some more on their good service to its guest. All the best & from the bottom of our hearts, Merci bou coup for a wonderful stay!

Really enjoyed my stay at the hotel. The hotel is situated in a great location, across the road you will find some wonderful pattiserie's. We stayed in room 332 located which ws tucked away and meant minimum noise. The rooms were quite spacious, especially for a Paris hotel. I really enjoyed the free coffee in the downstairs area, I found this area very relaxing and had a nice vibe. I would 100% return to this hotel as it's staff were very friendly, location was excellent and is all you really need for a city break.

Positives:

- staff very polite and friendly
- room was clean and good size
- hotel in a good location, lots of bars and restaurants. Felt very safe walking around in evening. Approximately 20 minute walk to Louvre and 40 minute-1 hour walk to main sights.

Negatives:

-breakfast was very limited, and staff started to pack away/remove food during operating hours.
-no bar on site, but there is a small supermarket over the road if you wish to pick up some drinks for your room.

Overall a good stay, but expected a bit more for the price we paid.

The hotel is located conveniently in walking distance from all major historical attractions. This is the only benefit of this hotel. Rooms are extremely small and noisy. The hotel staff is pretty rude. Breakfasts are more than frugal. If you pay approximately 250 euro per night you normally expect more.

The room is clean. The room size is larger than my expectation probably due to layout. The staff are friendly without overdone in services. The price is reasonable under its city centre location and booked at this period.

Excellent location, close to two metro lines and lots of lively restaurants. Staff were very friendly and room (513) was good too. And roomy by Parisian standards.

Read other reviews about street noise (very limited as the hotel installed two separate windows), thin mattress (topper on box springs - was fine) and noise from other rooms (a little but nothing too bad considering the hotel is in an old building). Room size and location might make a difference, we were fine though.

Would stay here again.

The hotel is very well-located in a street with lot of restaurants. The Moulin Rouge is within walking distance (17 minutes away). There are bus stops (bus 85) and a metro nearby (M7). The staff is super friendly.

We were due to stay three nights we left after one. Room was nothing like the pictures. Mattress was just a thin topper, only 1 pillow and 1 towel provided per person, we asked for extras and were told no. The towels are thin, only paper cups given. The aircon we very noisy and kept us awake. This was not like a normal Ibis, very below standard.

Perfect base to explore the city. As we knew we had booked a budget hotel, we were pleased to find that it was clean and comfortable. We requested a quiet room and got a room that was facing an interior courtyard so there was no noise. Staff were very friendly and managed to find us a room to check in early when we arrived before 2pm. The metro is nearby and it was very easy to get from the hotel to the Roissybus to CDG and also to the Big Red Bus stop for a sightseeing tour. It is within walking distance to the Louvre (20 min) and Montmartre (20 min). Op√©ra itself is a lovely area. I would stay here again.

Spent 5 nights and had a comfortable stay. The staff were nice and helpful. The location was great. Near the opera. Very close to 3-4 metro stations. Lots of restaurants and caf√©s. Spoilt for choice to eat. A couple of very good boulangeries nearby like Julien. Wish the rooms had a tea/ coffee station and a safe. However both these were available at the reception, so we managed. The Ac regulator didn‚Äôt work so it got freezing cold in the middle of the night. Other than that we had no problems.

Stayed here for three nights. Perfect location with plenty of restaurants and cafes nearby. Rooms are clean & perfectly fine for a short break. We were street side so there was some noise during the night but I would expect this. We found the staff very friendly and easy to deal with. Will return and have no hesitation in recommending.

I will start by saying that this is the second time we choose this hotel in the past year and we are strongly considering it again for our next trip to Paris. This is mainly because of the great location: it has (at least) 2 metro stations nearby (Grands Boulevards and Peletier) but if you prefer walking, you can get to the city center quite fast - Louvre is only 20 minutes away. Also, there are lots of good restaurants and bars around the hotel which are open until late so the area is also suitable for a walk in the evening without being overcrowded.
Some other things I appreciated during my visits: the staff is very friendly and helpful and the hotel is always clean.
Breakfast is simple but good, but, unfortunately, when the hotel is fully booked there is a strong chance you will have to wait a bit before finding a table. Also, the rooms are not very big and some of them don't have any view, but this is not something unusual for Paris.
Overall, I think the value for money here is great and it should be definitely considered as an option by anyone traveling to Paris on a budget.

Fab location ,if a little noisy at night . Rooms were good ,higher floors were great for people watching with the big windows wide open as rooms were a little warm . Fab resturants nearby too . Friendly staff and a great welcome

This was a good hotel, clean and functional with a good breakfast.

We stayed here with our teenage daughter for one night en-route back to England from Spain, mainly for its proximity to Gare du Nord which is around a 20 minute walk.

The room was ok although the reason I‚Äôve given it 4 stars was because firstly the air conditioning wasn‚Äôt switched on. Apparently this is the hotel‚Äôs policy - they only switch it on at a certain time of the year so as a warm spring day in April, we could have done with a/c to cool things down. It did have opening windows, but it was noisy with them open all night.

Secondly, there was no ability to make a hot drink in the room. I know this is at the budget end of the scale, but it would‚Äôve been nice (and expected) to have had something in the room to be able to make a cup of tea or coffee.

However, the hotel was in a good location, not far from the Moulin Rouge and it was only a short cab ride for us to get to the Montmartre. There were loads of cafes/restaurants nearby so you‚Äôd never be short of something to eat and drink close to the hotel.

We had breakfast the next morning and this was tasty and fresh - all of the usual pastries, bread and fruit were available, along with freshly made pancakes plus the ability to cook your own eggs.

Overall a good location, nice decor in the common areas and a decent enough budget hotel. Just a couple of small things that let it down a little bit.

The hotel is located in th Opera area, 5 minutes walk from the Galleries Lafayette.Next to Metro Lepeletier/Cadet or Notre Dame de Lorette. There are good restaurants all around.
The rooms are modern with a very good sleep quality and outstanding cleaness.
The personal is very kind.
I love the excellent breakfast buffet !

This hotel was wonderful!!! Super clean, quiet and the breakfast was a great start every day. The coffee bar was also open 24/7 for self serve so I could have a cup of coffee/tea/hot chocolate after dinner. The location was excellent, we would absolutely stay here again!

Beware. Hotel in Paris was supposed to refund us at the end of October because of a reservation that fell through due to pandemic and never did. They have stolen hundreds of dollars from us and do not care. Never again. I strongly recommend any other Hotel.

The location is amazing. very close to restaurants, supermarkets, caffeterias, bars, and subway stations. The staff is very kind, prepared and attenciously. That's the best part of the Ibis. The room was clean properly.

The hotel is in a wonderful location, close to the Opera and if you like walking, you can get to the Louvre, Montmartre, etc. Metro is closed too (Cadet, Le Peletier, Grand Boulevards). Our room was not so big but clean and in line with the Ibis standards i have experienced in other Countries. Unfortunately, our room was facing the courtyard and there was a constant buzz, perhaps from some extractor fans (?). It was bearable with closed windows, but with the open window it drove us crazy. On the arrival as we realised about the noise we ask for a room change that was not possible. I would suggest to ask for a room facing the street if you are staying over summer needing to open windows. Also, if you are a light sleeper, make sure you get a quite room before booking.

We were only staying in Paris for one night, in transit, and we chose the hotel due to its location and price.

The room was exactly what you'd expect at an Ibis but the staff were outstanding, friendly and helpful even when we checked in in the middle of the night.

The location is also great, close to lots of bars and restaurants and with easy access to the metro, buses and Gare du Nord.

Staff are really nice and helpful. Rooms were clean. Breakfast was really good. Didn't have A LOT of choices but I am sure has something for everybody as it was delicious. The hotel itself is really nicely decorated and well located. You have access to the metro nearby. I recommend this hotel for a nice weekend trip!

I was on a business trip to paris, and Ibis is my first choice as businessman.
This hotel was great when it came to staff (100% of them!) and location and even breakfast.
However, the walls were very thin and I could hear EVERYTHING that was done in the rooms, on the other side of the walls.
I'm sensetive to sounds so it bothered be a bit
Besides that the hotel was perfect!

The staff made me feel welcome and unique! Loved their service!

Staff friendly and room clean and practical. Found it just a little too hot in the room.
I only have one major comment on the material of the matras cover. Even under the bed sheets the material is plasticky and makes you sweat. Really NOT nice.

We spent a beautiful time in Paris and also at this hotel. The personnel is very kind, helps you if you need. A great location of the hotel, the bus station for Luvru museum at 2 minutes from the hotel.
We spent a great time.

Best place to stay, strategy location, friendly staff. Easy to find, Uber and Bus easy to reach. Metro as well. Walking disctance to lafayette shopping. take bus to moulin rouge and walking to Sacr√©-C≈ìur, Paris

The rooms are clean and comfortable. The hotel is in central and fantastic location in walking distance to main tourist attractions. The staff was very helpful. versatile and good value breakfast. I would happily stay there again while in short break in Paris.

Second time I have stayed in the hotel; I am sure there will be many more times. Very friendly and welcoming staff. Small but nice room that is functional for work (desk, light, wifi). Lies in a lively area of Paris not too far from The Louvre.

Our four night stay was enjoyable and comfortable. The hotel is within walking distance of 4 metro lines, and the surrounding area is vibrant and lively with lots of eateries. Our room was small but the windows opened and we could overlook the streets below. The staff were friendly and efficient and always welcoming. A small cafe sold pastries and coffee and there was a cozy sitting area. This is a budget hotel and amenities in the room were limited.

Good location near shopping places, walkable distance to main tourisric attractions and sites. Nearby bars and restaurants. clean property and modern, poor but tasty breakfast could add some exrra items. friendly staff

Our 4th floor, triple room was bigger than we had expected for the price we paid and location of this quiet, tidy hotel.
The location is perfect as it is close to the metro and many locations on foot. A sweet local neighbourhood on rue de Fauberg Monmartre.
Staff were very accommodating and helpful. We had 2 minor issues: our checkin was delayed past 3pm; and our room keys would only work intermittently.

Location was okay. Breakfast was good too. the staff are friendly too. The rest was average (i.e rooms, amenities not much). However i had a great time with the guidance of the staff on activities to do and how to move around with public transport.

The hotel was easy to find from the Gard du Nord, areas has nice restaurants and is easy to get to the major tourist sites of Paris.
Our rooms were in the, I think, older part of the hotel. 4 rooms on each floor. Decent sized room with everything you need.
The sound proofing of the rooms wasn't great, you could hear other people moving around. Not enough to spoil things for us but something to be aware of.
Very nice, helpful and friendly staff.

Small room, no view, extremely noisy air conditioning. Extremely expensive given location, rooms and overall comfort. Staff was however very friendly. Also, I had to pay in advance, which is rare, and my Accorhotels status was not taken into account. A very disappointing experience.

The hotel was close to the Metro so easy to get around sight seeing. Within walking distance of numerous cafes and restaurants.
The hotel itself was great, we had a good sized room which was great as we had three suitcases! Breakfast was very good. Staff very friendly and helpful.

As usual we had a nice stay in this hotel. This room in the loft however was too low and should not have been charged the same price as for standard rooms. As always the staff was very friendly and we enjoyed breakfast.

I don't have any complains. The hotel is what I expected in terms of an Accor hotel. Clean, well located, good staff, confortable bed. I didn't have the breakfast so I can't avaluate that. It is very close to a metro station, also close to good restaurantes, cafes and a really nice boulangerie.

The hotel is in a very nice location in Paris.
Room size is ok but room is really basic with no fridge and when I even asked about shaving kit you had to pay for it despite the very high price I paid.

There is renovation currently going on with no real reception but with no noise.

I have to review this on the basis it's a budget hotel. In that respect it's not bad and I really enjoyed this hotel.

(+) The key advantages of the hotel are its location ‚Äì on a lively street not far from Galeries Lafayette ‚Äì and metro stations (Grands Boulevards and Le Peletier).

(-) The staff services could be improved, obe thing that surprised me was we had to come to the reception area (around 9PM during our stay) to get new bath-soap bottle (since probably the housekeeping staff missed to check it). Room was kinda located under 2 staircase and in an attic since the ceiling is quite low.

Good location
Good price/quality relation
Noisy neighboors and very unrespectful (room 105 on the 10th of March) I had to ask 3 times for them to be quite and still they were not respectful.
Despite of this incident everything's fine

The hotel is perfectly located, close to several metro stations and in an area where you can easily find a nice restaurant for an evening meal on walking distance. Room is clean and comfortable, staff very friendly.

I have to review this on the basis it's a budget hotel. In that respect it's not bad, though did pay a heft price over christmas. The room for 3 of us was surprisingly roomy for paris. No fridge or facilities, but loved that you could go down and make a machine latte or coffee...not obvious but just go to the breakfast lounge and make yourself. cups are under the cupboard. Breakfast very average but sufficient. Location good with metro near.

Thought that is within a short walking distance from Op√©ra House, but indeed it took a bit of time to walk. Neighbourhood is rather rough. One good thing is the staff - friendly and helpful. Hotel room is clean but not so well maintained.

for breakfast, music should be fine. Really big silent . no music. too silencious. finally I got y breakfast outside. I will prefer baguette for bread . good reception , fine employees , helpful and kind .

The hotel was only 10 minutes walk from Galeries Lafayette and Palais Garnier.

There were plenty of restaurants around the hotel. A supermarket was just across the street.

The room we were given was pretty big by Paris standard. The room sizes were different so it‚Äôs a matter of chance what you ended up with.

Staff were friendly and overall it‚Äôs a nice stay.

Arrival and registration were quick and efficient. I was expected and allocated my room without problems. The room itself was as expected at an IBIS, simple but everything you need is there. Plenty of power points, so I could use my computer and charge my phone at the same time. WiFi was free and worked well. The bathroom is small, but plenty of hot water and a powerful shower.My only complaint is that the windows opened onto a space between two buildings and you couldn't really even see the sky. The windows had frosted glass, so as long as you didn't open them, you could imagine the Eiffel Tower somewhere in the distance.Breakfast was better than you get in many Parisian hotels, with fresh fruit and yoghurt as well as the standard croissants and bread. I would stay again if in Paris and needed to be close to the Gare du Nord.

Hotel location is great in the city with a room for 3 adults. Around the hotel is a lot of restaurants and u can reach attractive places walking. The bathroom is very good. Metro station is very near. Location is beside the opera and shopping street.

What a great hotel to explore Paris! The location is excellent, close to the centre of Paris giving easy access to all the sights and attractions. The immediate area has plenty of bars and is very lively.
It is true that the rooms are quite cramped and basic, but this is a low budget Ibis and represents great value for money. The rooms and all public areas are spotlesly clean and the breakfast, whilst basic, is perfectly acceptable.
Highly recommend this hotel, but you must understand the limitations which the low prices impose. We will use it again.

Convenient hotel if travelling by Eurostar to and from Gare de Nord. Hotel appears tired, but in the main everything else is fine. Plenty of eateries and bars within a short walk. Good value for money.

Very bad hotel. They steal your money. They told me to pay 99 euros before i came to them from Amsterdam as security which i did pay but they said they will refund it once i check-out. It has been a month now and everytime i call them they say sir it only takes a few days and let us ask the manager and the GM doesn‚Äôt even have the audacity to call and atleast talk with me in regards to it i am limited to some call center they have which is based in some African Country. I even sent them my personal accounts transaction where it shows the money deducted and nothing refunded. I would seriously aware people to not go with such a hotel which has such an irresponsible staff and such a bad way of dealing and a worse management system. I STILL haven‚Äôt recovered my money and i don‚Äôt know where it went. And instead of sending me any proof they are instead sending me marketing messages! Shame on you people!

Great location (15-20min nice walk to Louvre area; 10-12 min to Montmartre,5min to Metro) around an area full of bars and restaurants; decent size of bedroom (we were 3 friends and thought it was comfortable) and actually ‚Äúbig‚Äù bathroom (for Parisien stds); it‚Äôs a great quality-price option. The staff was nice and I was even happily surprised one of then spoke Portuguese (I‚Äôm Brazilian).Very consistent with the Ibis brand, no unpleasant surprises. Would definitely stay there again.

I initially had a bit of a hard time finding the place, but afterwards noted my way and was very close to the Grands Boulevards and the Opera. This hotel offered great value for money, Even if it is smack in the middle of town , you dont hear a thing thanks to 2 double windows. The room was quite ok (Ibis standard) as well as the breakfast (continental). I would definitely go back there if I stayed in Paris.

We just stayed in this Ibis for one night when on a citytrip in Paris. The best thing about the hotel is definitely the location. It's close to everything and the neighbourhood is pleasant, even late at night. The room was small but very nice. Super comfortable bed! Would stay here again. I see some comments on rude staff but we had no problems whatsoever as we were helped by staff in a very friendly manner.

First of all, the location of the hotel is great, but that's about it.

The rooms are small as f***, dirty (I found hair on the bed and the carpet) and are strongly in need of a renovation.

But the worst of it all are the receptionists. The check-in was handled by a young gentleman. You could see it in his face that he wasn't enjoying his work at all.

I asked him, if he could bring uns some hotel slip-on shoes and he said "Yes", he would bring them later to the room.

Some three hours later, the shoe weren't brought, so I went back downstairs to the reception.

The young gentleman was gone and an old one was sitting there. I asked him in French about the shoes, he didn't answer. Then again in English, and he just plain and simple said "No". He didn't even look at me!

I have never seen such unfriendly hotel employees in ANY country (and I have been to many and also stayed in many Parisien hotels)

The Hotel is at a good location and walking distance to many nice locations in Paris - eg Sacre Coeur Basilica, Galleries Lafayette / Printemps, Chartier and lots of nice cafes which Paris is famous for.

However as an Accor Platinum member; I was pretty disappointed the lack of amenities to my room nor was I entitled to room upgrade, nor the welcome; warm.

Clearly the hotel staff were overwhelmed when we checked in 8 pm on a Friday night.

Was also the same when I patronised another Ibis in Munich, maybe they do not recognize Platinum members much.

ibis grands-a boulangerie, 24 hour cocci grocery, restaurant just outside the outside the front door, what else do you need?
room is big, i mean not cramped-paris standard, staying on the 4th floor, breakfast is dear though, wc is cramped, beds are okay, for around ‚Ç¨100 cant complain,ill stay here again sure

Having stayed here many times, saddened Given the wrong key, helped immediately but first impression not good. Also after doing away with little soaps etc, tubes of liquid soap not replaced after 3 days, had to go and point this oui at desk. breakfast still fine but impression of skimping only one of two energy saving bulbs in the lamps was operating in the dining area.

I traveled with my family, and we were a total of 6 - they were very accommodating to us, giving us rooms next to each other. The daily included breakfast was delicious! And the staff spoke many langueages, which was helpful for all.

First of all, the carpet in the room was really dirty, and the noise cancelling doesn't exist even on the fifth floor.
Unfriendly and rude staff..

The main issue is about security : faulty lock, door working badly, useless security cameras since most of the rooms are located in their blind spot...

We were robbed in our room as well as other guests in the hotel the same day (computer, branded accessories)...

The Hotel manager is in charge of the security of the guests inside the Hotel! It is definitely not the case at "Ibis Paris Grands Boulevards Opera"!!

It is shameful for such an hotel group!

I strongly advise against this hotel.

Clean rooms and comfy stay. There are lots of Ibises in Paris but I think this one was the best in terms of value for money and location. You can walk to most attractions in 15 mins. Convenience store and cafes just outside.

The rooms were small, but cosy. Bathroom were clean. Might need to address some plumbing issues (they came to fix it promptly during our stay).

We booked during the peak season (July) but still managed to get reasonable rates and came with free breakfast (accor promo). Breakfast was very good and had a variety of items to choose from, though I probably wouldn't have opted for breakfast if it wasn't complementary -- there are heaps of cafes around.

Staff were very courteous and spoke very good English, depending on who you get, but speaking French to staff will get you A+++ service. Like most Accor hotels the standards are quite high, address all questions/concerns promptly, clean and up to date.

The rooms were extremely small. We had to complain after three days to change the sheets and towels. At breakfast Nutella finished and for three days they didn t have any. The lobby id unpleasant. The only positive is that at least the personnel tries to be friendly and the good internet connection.

I stayed two nights, and went off outside Paris one day, when coming back for my next stay, a very bad room was allocated to me, so small that I can barely move around. The reception desk asked me to wait one night to change room the next day. Next day, a message was logged into the reception desk books, but nobody attended to it. Back from my day meetings, I have been told that nobody took care of the needful, and I had to wait one more day again! Reception desk members took the matter very lightly, and they did not seem to care at all. Personally, I just feel customers are being taken for a ride here, and the reception desk members just find a way not to take customer comments into account. This is definitely not a Ibis hotel I will recommend at all to all my members working in our group of companies, and I will definitely need to indicate the bad service and bad response of the reception desk of this Hotel.

Location and good value for money if booked in early. Good wi-fi, 100 m from metro station ( Av. Lafayete )
Good accommodations ( Ibis standard ); Modern hotel. Friendly and attentive service.
You can store your bags after check out for 2 euros.

I have just spent 4 days in this hotel (room 504).

All staff are really nice and helpful, the room was very clean and calm (just small, but this is the standard in Paris) and breakfast adequate. Nice also the internet corner.

Its central location is helpful reach walking many touristic places.

The worst? Having to leave to come back to work to Italy, but I do hope to come back!

it is a good choice for people want to stay at city center , near metro and bus station . there is a shuttle bus at opera can take u to airport .
wi fi is free . breakfast is simple .
the drawbacks are the elevator is not working at time of stay , but the staff help us to get a room at 1st floor , another thing there is no mini bar and in July we need minibar
otherwise we enjoy our stay in this hotel ,thanks for everyone who helped us

This hotel is perfect if you're in Paris looking for a place to rest after a long day of touristing around the city. Roms are small but clean. It's very close to metro station with a crepe/ice cream place (loved it)
No mini bar in room and the hotel doesn't really sell anything if you're looking for a snack late at night but there are plenty of fast food and food markets on the same street.

Great stay, quiet, comfy beds, easy to walk everywhere lovely spot. Staff helpful with locations and trips. Shower hot. Clean towels each day. We didn't have breakfast but that was an option 15 minutes walk from the GDN station

We had chosen this hotel (knowing very well how warm it can be in Paris end of May) because it announced having AC. Much to our surprise it didn't work allthough the outside outside temperature was some 30 degrees. No reaction from personnel when complaining about this, it was obvious that we were not the first ones to complain. The room was room ok, breakfast reasonable, but not being able to sleep well because of the heat means we will never book there again.

Exactely as all Ibis. Clean. Good location, but a very small room (In Paris it looks like standard).
The location was the best point. Probably one of the best region for travelers. Very close to Opera (picture) and Galery Lafayet.

I was quite disappointed with my stay here. I've stayed at Ibis hotels before and have always liked them but unfortunately this was not good. The staff weren't particularly friendly, the room was pokey, the air conditioning was broken so the room was incredibly hot and the bed was utterly woeful and uncomfortable.

If you stay at an Ibis hotel, you can expect "budget" expecience - and that is what you get here. A clean room and bath, good beds and more or less silence. The location of this Ibis is good and convenient for visiting the Opera and the magasins (2 metro stops away), and the neighborhood is full of shops (books, stamps, furniture...), bars and you name it.

We had a triple room facing the front of the hotel and the group found the bed very comfortable and the room bigger than expected. Despite the fact that our room faced the street, we had absolutely no noise issues. It also has a nice bathroom and it's very clean.

The staff is very friendly and polite, and since the hotel doesn't serve lunch or dinner, we were easily able to use the breakfast area for a group dinner. We also found out that if anyone needs hot water for tea, it's possible to get it at any time in the breakfast area (by the way, there's also a microwave that any guest is allowed to use).

The location is very convenient, as it's not only close to metro station Le Peletier - line 7 - (there's another metro station reasonably close, Grands Boulevards - lines 8 and 9) but very close to Montmartre as well. There are many shops (including a Carrefour), boulangeries and restaurants near the hotel, and a local shop across the street with a good selection of fruits.

It serves a good continental breakfast and the lady running the breakfast was extremely sweet and caring, despite the language barrier.

The Hotel did not live up to a standard which we expect from Ibis. The staff did not display any sense that they worked there on a regular basis. The breakfast room staff were excellent and accomodating

This hotel is ideally located for exploring central paris. It is within walking distance (20 mins) of the Eurostar Gare du Nord, near the metro and in a very pleasant area of shops, restaurants and shopping arcades. Our double room was of a good size, very clean and with a large comfortable bed. Breakfast had a reasonable choice of food which we purchased on arrival at 10 euros per person - its cheaper if you book in advance. The staff were all very friendly and helpful. We will definitely stay here again.

Located in the city center but no parking facilities.
Old, dusty and small room but with very comfortable shower and bed!
Breakfast & staff in general are according to hotel level without any bad or good surprises ...

Stayed in the Ibis for 2 nights over the weekend. Very comfortable bed and nice bathroom. The check in was very easy. Not the easiest metro station or view but generally well appointed. Would recommend it to a friend.

Nice, clean and friendly staff with affordable rate, within minutes to get breakfast, lunch or dinner out side (cafes surrounding). For you who enjoy vegetarian food, try Vegebow resto, near this hotel location, 5-7 minutes walk, lovely dishes with reasonable price.

The good Ibis standards can be easily seen in this hotel. Wifi works very well and the room (614) was spacious and clean. I just suggest you take a look at the elevator - it produces a strange sound, as if the ropes were about to collapse!.

We like this hotel as it is very well positioned for most of the places we like to go to in Paris. You can walk to the hotel from Gare du Nord and it is easy to walk to Montmartre, Les Halles, the Opera and the Seine. The breakfast here is of a very high quality and the staff are friendly and efficient. This is very good value for money.

We booked the place last minute for 5 nights during Jun'16. Although the located seemed great with lots of restaurants/pubs etc nearby. I believe we booked last minute hence the high tariff. Staff was nice and helpful. Room was decent compared to most European hotels. Proximity to 2 metro station made this place great.

First of all, as usual the room is standard for almost all Ibis ! I like the location and restaurant is easy to find along the road.

Things to improve:

1) Complementary water
2) write pad and pen
3) Safety box
4) Breakfast to serve hot meal!

Initially, they put us in a room in the old building of the hotel which was too small and definitely didn't live up to a 3-star hotel. There was literally no room for two people going around in the room, the decoration was sad, there was no natural light...We didn't exactly inspect the room in detail because we felt they definitely had to change us rooms immediately.
The good thing is that as soon as we asked them, they happily changed us rooms. The new room was in the attic so again a bit smaller but much better. However, it was located just next to the elevator so it was getting noisy at times.
We only had one pair of towels while we were two people and at some point we ran out of soap and there was no replacement.
The cleanliness was OK.
Breakfast was decent but again not the same level as other ibis hotels I have stayed.
The people in the reception were very nice and polite.

This hotel is close to metro stations, main boulevards and walking distance attractions. It is a good value hotel and decent service. I walked to many places from there and/or took the metro to go around the city.

The hotel is located somewhere halfway between Gare du Nord and Opera which is quite convenient, with of course many metro stations around. I had a quiet room under the roof with shower bathroom, and as everywhere in Paris do not expect much space. Friendly and efficient check-in. Breakfast gives a nice choice of viennoiseries, limited hot dishes and fruit (salad) among others in a neat square room

We were here for a week. I really liked the hotel happy to go back and I will return! The room was very nice clean look in our window but the streets are well insulated. The breakfast is perfect for me but I think my dad would be varied according delicious! The cards also broke down the door several times but it was resolved quickly at the reception. The staff is very kind to everyone ;) I can not wait to go back! (Sorry Google translate)

Busy location.
Boulangerie and supermarkets nearby.
Small and old hotel.
Elevator is slow.
Can use a bidet in the toilet.
Can use a hairdryer upgrade.

Locked hotel doors at night.
One-man team during the night shift.
Room key card kept messing up and had to be reprogrammed almost everyday.

Frances and the gentleman with salt and pepper colored hair were helpful and accommodating. The white-haired man was a bit curt.
The housekeeping lady was very nice, even with the language barrier.

Trouble at checkout because reception was insisting we ordered breakfast at the hotel but we did not. Cafe staff came in and confirmed our group did not order breakfast.

I stayed in this hotel in August.
I arrived late at night but the receptionist welcomed us very warmly.
The room isn't very big but when you're in paris you don't see your room a lot :)
The breakfast was ok.
2 thumbs up for the older lady running the breakfast area ! She was so nice, looking after the customers and making sure everything was refilled !

Negatives of the hotel:
When the room is cleaned they leave the door open. I myself Worked as a supervisor in a hotel and I used to tell the staffmembers not to do this. Everyone can see the what is inside the room...
the locker system was something I didn't like. You have to pay to storage your luggage once you've checked out. It was the first time i saw this service Being charged

I will begin with the positives -

* Location - the hotel 's position is great for visiting all of the major sights either by metro or on foot. It is close to several metro stations, the closest being Le Peletier. There are shops, cafes and restaurants in the immediate vicinity of the hotel ( good job but more of that later). A short and pleasant stroll brings you to the wonderful Galleries Lafayette and many other shops including Sephora and H&M and of course the Opera House.

* Cleanliness - the whole hotel was cleaned to a good standard. Our room was cleaned well everyday during our visit. All the communal areas which I saw were clean.

*Reception staff - this falls into both categories as most of the staff were friendly and helpful (unless the electronic key stopped working which it did on more than one occasion).

That's the positives - sadly the negatives outweigh the positives by a considerable margin. I will begin with our arrival at the hotel -

* Reception staff - it took sometime to check us in as the reception staff seemed a little confused. Not entirely his fault as there were 5 rooms booked under the same surname - (however, the initials were different). Once we had achieved this I asked of other members of our family had checked in and he seemed unable to tell whether they had or they hadn't. As my suitcase had been lost/ delayed I asked for a toothbrush etc and was told that the hotel doesn't provide these things! It is a 3 star hotel and I would expect them to have these for such occasions. I wasn't even told where I might buy them.

* Foyer- very few chairs in this area and not very welcoming. Our party was 8 and there was nowhere for us to sit altogether for a chat. The hotel does not have a lounge although there is a room which is used for breakfast and could quite easily be adapted for use as a lounge area during the rest of the day
*Maps/ information - unlike most other hotels I have stayed in this one did not provide any maps or other information about Paris and its attractions. There was no information about special events which were happening during the period we stayed there. I think for a 3 star hotel this is very poor.

*Lift - there was only one lift in the hotel and this often resulted in long waits to get to our floor especially when the cleaning staff were moving their equipment. It was impossible to access the stairs from the ground floor as the door was locked. The stairs themselves are very old and narrow and sloping and not easy to walk up and down.

* The room- was clean but rather on the small side and very basic. Apart from the bed there was nowhere to sit except for one plastic chair. There was a large TV too. I would have welcomed tea and coffee making facilities or at least a kettle so we could have a drink when we returned from a days sight seeing. If this wasn't possible then a drinks machine in the hotel would have made life easier. Instead we had to go to a coffee shop or cafe.
I was woken one morning by hat sounded like drilling but think it was either the air con or the hairdryer in one of the adjoining rooms. Not a good way to start the day!

* The bathroom- was very clean but I think to say toiletries were provided was stretching it somewhat. What they actually provided was two plastic bottles of liquid soap. These were fixed to the wall and could not be removed by guests. We used the last of the soap from the one in the shower on the first night but it was not replaced until the third day! Other than that there were no shower caps or body lotions etc. We were given one very small both towel each and no hand towels or flannels. The towels themselves were, in addition to being very small, very thin and not really three star standard.

I was surprised to see that the hotel did not have a room for storing luggage - instead you had to pay 2 euros for a locker!

The hotel was booked for us by another family member - had I been looking for a hotel I would not have chosen this one as there are many others in the same area of the city which offer better value for money.

We paid 3 star hotel prices for something which was, in my opinion, more like a motel. I wouldn't stay there again or recommend it to anybody.

the hotel was clean and our bedroom, although small, had a nice view. Nice bathroom! However, we had to carry our bags and suitcases through the stairs, because the lift does not go to 6th floor. nice breakfast too.

This is an older building that has been added to the IBIS brand, not a standard cookie cutter IBIS, so it has meandering corridors and odd shaped rooms. The staff were universally friendly, and the location could not be better. My only minor quibble is that at breakfast - the usual IBIS market of cheese, meats, breads etc, by 08.30 on both mornings of the stay, the only fruit was a couple of apples and oranges. Across the road the local shop had apricots, peaches, raspberries, strawberries and more. Come on IBIS!

Well located clean hotel though rooms are small and quadruple rooms open in inner courtyard staff friendly. Street has lots of super markets bakeries budget restaurants and cafes le petricheie metro station nearer than grand buelovards

The location of the hotel is great, about 5 minutes walk from the Metro station, and many restaurants near by. It's also a 15 minutes walking distance from Paris Gare de Nord, so it's a great location for those who travel from CDG airport.

the location is strategic. the food for breakfast is average, always the same every morning. boring. the staf is quite friendly. they seldom smile to guests. what a pity. the price is so so. I stayed here for the second time. and the breakfast is the same ever since. make better please!

We stayed here for 3 nights. The hotel is great and in a good location. The room was bigger than expected and the beds are comfy. There are lots of bars and restaurants nearby and Opera is about a 15 minute walk. We would stay here again.

Great all round place to stay!

We stayed for 4 nights as a family in a triple room on the 5th floor.

The location is brilliant, very near several metro stations, a short walk to Opera so perfect to explore Paris (the most beautiful old sweet shop is opposite and a must see, Gallereis Lafayette 5 mins walk away - what's not to like!) The street itself is fine with lots of handy shops nearby.

Our room was as expected, clean, comfy, a bit larger than some Ibis rooms I have stayed in before with very good daily maid service. Air-con worked a treat. Despite it being a huge chain, there was charm to this hotel as it was an old building with spiral stairs and a nicely quirky layout.

ALL the staff in this hotel were exceptional. The reception girls went out of their way to help us, they were genuinely friendly, efficient and made us feel very welcome. Big thanks for the football goodies and cold drinks they provided when we were slightly delayed at check in. The couple who run the breakfast room also deserve a special mention, they were absolutely charming, friendly and efficient (don't tell but my son called them Granny and Granddad Paris!!) The breakfasts were good (lots of choice buffet style).

The staff in this hotel are the icing on the cake, they go the extra mile which made our stay so good. Thank you so much, we would love to return.

This location is quite near the Cadet bus stop so getting back to hotel by bus is convenient. Carefour supermarket is nearby.

On the day of check-in, the room is not yet ready as another customer requested late check-out and they need time to clean the room, glad that the room is clean and they provided complimentary left buggage for check-in customer.

However, on the day of check-out, we were told that left luggage for check-out is not complementary and we need to use locker instead.

We don't want to hold the room for extra 1-2 hours (just to store our luggages) so next customer can have the room ready sooner but it is like we are "penalized" by not asking for late check-out.

Be sure book your train/air ticket departure by noon so you don't need to use their locker. With so many hotel stays (incl accors and ibis in other countries), this is the first time that hotel provide no left luggage service on check-out.

Also, as on par of ibis standard, no toothbrush and slippers in room so please be prepared if you want to book this hotel.

The Ibis Paris Grand Blvd is well located. My family and I are staying here now and have no complaints. The room is spacious. Comfortable beds. Friendly staff. Clean and well located near two different metro lines. Well priced. Nothing glamorous but very functional. Will definitely stay here again should the occasion arise.

Wonderfully located near metro, shopping and dining. Friendly service, clean hotel that serves a good continental breakfast.
Suited our family for the 3 days we were here. They even arranged for a Dr to visit us when our son was sick. The only reason I didn't give them a 4 star was due to the construction out our window that started at 5:00am üò° and a poorly working air conditioner.
